            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I have the exact same problem.\r\n\r\nOne thing I noticed is that if I type clear inside my terminal it will clear all the command I manually typed and their results.\r\nFor example if I type echo 'test' 5 times, 10 lines will be added (5x command and their output).\r\nIf I type clear, those 10 lines will be deleted.\r\n\r\nHowever if I ran some tests before every output from jest will still be inside the terminal.\r\nThe clear command only clear the command I have entered not jest output.\r\n\r\nAnd of course if jest is launched in watch mode, this will add lines and lines to the terminal each time it detect a change and rerun the tests.\r\n\r\nDoes anyone has some clue about this strange behaviour ?\r\n\r\n=> Just found out some more strangeness:\r\n- if I use bash then the terminal is correctly cleared by jest on each run\r\n- It happens that I use fish and if this shell is used inside of neovim terminal then it's impossible to clear jest output",
